d migration Monitor the external threat environment for new threats and advise relevant partners on the appropriate course of action Create a targeted information security awareness training program and establish metrics to measure the effectiveness of the program Coordinate the development and periodic testing of incident response plans and procedures Manage and contain information security incidents and events to protect company IT assets, intellectual property, regulated data and our reputation Maintain responsibility for management of assigned operations Required Qualifications: Bachelor's degree in business or a technology related field Professional security management certification, such as Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP), Certified Information Security Manager (CISM), Certified Information Security Auditor (CISA) or other similar credentials Ten years of progressive experience in a combination of risk management, information security and IT, with at least five years of experience in a management position Any equivalent combination of education, training, and experience that provides the skills necessary to perform the essential function of the job Must maintain valid Texas Driver's License, or available alternate means of transportation Knowledge of methodologies and trends in both business and IT Experience in cloud security implementation, management, policies and practices Track record and experience developing information security procedures, and experience securing cloud technologies Experience acting calmly and competently in high-pressure, high-stress situations Knowledge of relevant legal and regulatory requirements, such as: Sarbanes-Oxley Act (SOX), and Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) Knowledge of common information security management frameworks, such as ISO/IEC 27001, ITIL, COBIT and those from NIST, including 800-53 and Cybersecurity Framework Our Benefits: Day one health, dental, and vision insurance Performance bonus 401k plan with 4% basic employer contribution and 100% employer match contribution up to 6% Vacation, sick, holiday and volunteer time off Life and disability insurance Flexible spending account Free on-site gym and fitness classes Professional development Tuition reimbursement Pet insurance Free identity theft protection Company-sponsored social and philanthropy events Texas Mutual Insurance Company is an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. ",
